1.7.1
1. In an 8-bit binary number, which is the most significant bit (MSB)?
Thee left most number is the most significant bit, showing if the number is positive or negative

2.What is the decimal representation of each of the following unsigned binary integers?
a.00110101 is equal to 53
b.10010110 is equal to 150
c.11001100 is equal to 204

